com.radiantlogic.iddm.base

Interface SequentialDataProvider<OUT extends SearchResponse & HasStatus>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataProvider<OUT>, Response, SearchResponse

    public interface SequentialDataProvider<OUT extends SearchResponse & HasStatus>
extends DataProvider<OUT>
    This interface defines methods for providing responses with partial data, where the data can be accessed in only sequential order, similar to a singly linked list.

    To use, the developer needs to create a class that implements this interface and each of its methods (as no default implementations are provided). This interface is typically implemented by a delegate that is returned by the connector, rather than being implemented by the connector itself. For example: 

    
 class SearchResponseDelegate implements SequentialDataProvider<LdapResponse<String>> {

   public LdapResponse<String> next() {
    // ...implementation...
   }

   ...
 }

 class CustomConnector implements SearchOperations<LdapSearchRequest, Response> {

   public Response search(LdapSearchRequest request) {
     return new SearchResponseDelegate(request);
   }
 }
